            "datePublished": "04 Sep 2018 00:00:00 GMT",
            "about": "Long-planned reissue of Kawabata’s first solo LP, from way back in 2000 (about 100 releases ago, in Kawabata terms). Originally released by the mighty SIWA label in a tiny, hand printed edition of 300, this has long been the most sought-after Kawabata item, pretty much impossible to track down without a wallet full of ebay slush funds. The music, as on all of Kawabata’s INUI series releases, is intensely personal and introspective, with long tracks built up of soft-focus layers of mid-fi violin, sarangi, oud, sitar, bouzouki, etc. French film maker and musician Audrey Ginestet lends her crystal voice to “Shin.”",
            "credits": "released September 4, 2018\nKawabata Makoto: violin, sarangi, oud, sitar, bouzouki, lyra, shou, nei, voice, Audrey Ginestet: voice on “Shin”",
