            "datePublished": "16 Mar 2017 00:00:00 GMT",
            "about": "INUI 2 was the first widely available solo CD by this prolific Japanese guitarist/composer/bearded guru. Known primarily for his recent work with oddballs Acid Mothers Temple, Kawabata's career actually goes back to the late '70s and spans many styles, including solo guitar improv, electronics, folk, and, of course, the deranged acid mayhem associated with the PSF scene. Performed entirely solo on violin, kemenje, zurna, electronics, sarangi, taiko, gong, water, bouzouki, cello, vibes, organ, and sitar, the four tracks that make up INUI 2 are perfectly executed dream-music, equal parts delicately floating and heavily droning. There's also one all-too-short modal essay for bouzouki that is amazingly beautiful.",
            "credits": "released March 16, 2017\nKawabata Makoto:\n1: Violin, kemenje, zurna, electronics\n2: Sarangi, taiko, gong, water\n3: bouzouki, cello, vibe, organ\n4: bowed sitar, violin, electric sitar, electronics\nComposed by Kawabata Makoto\nRecorded at Acid Mothers Temple 11th-15th February 2000\nEngineered by Kawabata Makoto\nart work by ELF",
